rComments: Ummm and aaaahh soooo ummmm aaaah yeah :(

This class is very uninspiring and somehow manages to make learning about neural networks boring. Assignments/homeworks are relentless (1 per week, each taking 10hrs to complete). The lectures are boring - straight reading from the slides. In summary, quality and attention to details is completely lacking and not fitting of a top tier school.

Weekly homework takes about 10 hours for an average student. TAs are super unresponsive: as of today, there are about twenty un-answered questions on Piazza and no TA responds since 4-days ago. The professor is insightful but he expects all the students to be as insightful as him. Worth to AUDIT though since the troubles are related to marking part
Our professor is very knowledgable and strong at research, but I hope he can put more effort into teaching in the future.

Always read slides. Jimmy is a good researcher, but apparently he doesn't have a willingness to prepare for teaching. Concepts are given too vague without examples. I learned most of the materials online by watching other professors' youtube courses.
Teaching style is very uninspiring. Uses slides a lot almost no use of black board.
